6. Rights to Access, Correction, and Deletion of Personal Information
You may have legal rights to request access, correct, restrict, port, copy, or delete your personal information, or withdraw your consent. Upon your request to withdraw consent, we will stop processing your personal information. However, such withdrawal will not affect the processing of personal information previously covered by your consent. A request to withdraw consent, restrict or stop processing your information, or delete your account or information may result in your inability to access the Services or some of its features. Please note that even if you delete your personal information from us, we may retain your personal information to comply with laws and for other purposes described in Section 3(b) of this Privacy Policy.
If you wish to exercise your legal rights or any parents or legal guardians wish to exercise the rights on behalf of their children, you may submit a verifiable request to us via email at [PRIVACY@NPIXEL.CO.KR]. If verified, we will provide the information unless doing so proves impossible or would involve a disproportionate effort. You might be asked to provide additional information to verify that the person making the request is the same person about whom we collected information. This additional information will be used solely for verification purposes.
7. Retention of Personal Information
We will only retain your personal information as long as you continue to use the Services, or for as long as is necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. Please note that even if you delete your personal information from us, we may retain a copy of your personal information to comply with laws and for other purposes described in Section 3(b) of this Privacy Policy
8. Protection Measures of Personal Information; International Transfer
We take appropriate technical security safeguards to protect your information from unauthorized access, destruction, use, modification or disclosure. However, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information we collect from you, as the Internet by its nature is not a secure environment. If you choose to share your information with us, please be reminded of such risk.
By using our services or otherwise providing us with personal information, you agree to send and process your information internationally. When transferring personal information outside, we implement technical, organizational and physical protection to protect your personal information.
9. For California Residents
For California residents, your rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) are:
                                    right to request disclosure of personal information, right to request deletion of personal information, right to prevent the sale of personal information, and protection against discrimination.
a. Categories of Personal Information We Collect and Share.
